V. Limiting Behavior
The TRR framework has four well-defined limits, each recovering a known physical regime. This section documents them explicitly to establish that the theory is constrained rather than tunable.
5.1 GR Limit: ε → 0
As ε → 0, the mode-sector transition radius r_c → r_s. All ℓ ≥ 1 modes become evanescent everywhere outside the horizon.
•	Love number: k₂ ∝ ε² → 0. Objects become tidally rigid (black hole limit in GR).
•	Echo delay: Δt_echo = 2r_s ln(1/ε) → ∞. Echoes shift to infinite delay, i.e., no echo.
•	Echo amplitude: R_GW ~ exp(−c/ε) → 0. No reflected power.
•	QNM shift: δω/ω_GR ~ π/ln(1/ε) → 0. Ringdown frequencies converge to Kerr values.
In this limit TRR is observationally indistinguishable from GR. Current data require ε < 1.49 × 10⁻⁶, placing the theory within this convergent regime.
5.2 No-Breathing-Mode Limit: λ → 0
As λ → 0, the Mexican hat potential flattens. The effective scalar mass m_eff² = 2λΨ₀² → 0. Consequences:
•	Breathing mode frequency f_s ∝ √λ → 0. The scalar excitation becomes massless and the breathing mode disappears from the sub-kHz GW band.
•	The Yukawa screening length m_Y⁻¹ = c/√(2λ)Ψ₀ → ∞. Substrate perturbations propagate without mass suppression at all scales.
•	The Poisson equation ∇²C = −κρ is unaffected. Gravity remains intact.
This limit is not observationally excluded but pushes the breathing mode below current detector sensitivity. λ → 0 is a consistent subspace of TRR.
5.3 Saturation Limit: κ_max → 1
κ_max → 1 corresponds to maximum coherence saturation — the substrate coherence approaches its vacuum expectation value everywhere inside the compact object. In this limit:
•	Breathing mode: f_b = (3.8/√κ_max) f_tensor → 3.8 f_tensor. The breathing frequency reaches its maximum relative to the tensor mode.
•	Interior structure: The smooth-branch solution approaches a constant-density coherence profile. The compact object's interior is maximally coherent.
•	Stability: The stability condition κ < κ_max is marginally satisfied everywhere. Objects at this limit are at the boundary of the allowed parameter space.
The observational bound κ_max > 0.95 from breathing mode non-detection places the theory below this saturation boundary.
5.4 Classical Gravity Limit: ω_c → ∞
As ω_c → ∞, the carrier wavelength λ_c = 2πc/ω_c → 0. The substrate oscillates infinitely fast compared to any physical timescale.
•	Timing residual: σ(Δt) ~ GM_⊕L/(ω_c² c² R_⊕³) → 0. Coherence fluctuations in clock synchronization vanish.
•	SVEA validity: The slowly-varying envelope approximation becomes exact. The substrate appears as a static coherence background.
•	Carrier effects: Any ω_c-dependent signature (timing correlations, sideband structure) vanishes.
•	GR recovery: In this limit TRR is equivalent to classical Newtonian/GR gravity with no substrate signatures.
The optical clock lower bound ω_c > 1.4 × 10¹⁵ rad/s establishes that the theory is not in this limit, but the current bound is still three orders of magnitude below the ultraviolet (UV) regime.



